#MEM id=references source=/root/yvon/agent-department/COO/diana/skills/marketplace/lean-startup/references/small-batches.md savings=2%
M|Smal|tx|The power of small batches is counterintuitive. Most people believe working in large batches is more efficient bc it minimizes setup time and context switching. In reality, small batches dramatically reduce cycle time, catch problems earlier, reduce risk, and accelerate learning. This principle, borrowed from lean manufacturing, is one of the most practical and immediately applicable ideas in the Lean Startup.
M|The |Imag|
M|The |**La|** Fold all 100 letters, then stuff all 100 envelopes, then seal all 100, then stamp all 100, then address all 100.
M|The |**Sm|** Take one envelope through the entire process (fold, stuff, seal, stamp, address), then move to the nx.
M|The |tx|Most people intuitively believe the large batch approach is faster. They are wrong.
M|The |**Wh|**
M|The |tx|\| Factor \| Large Batch \| Small Batch \|
M|The |tx|\|--------\|-------------\|-------------\|
M|The |tx|\| Total time \| Longer (measured repeatedly in experiments) \| Shorter \|
M|The |tx|\| er detection \| er found at the very end; must redo entire batch \| er found immediately; fix one item \|
M|The |tx|\| Work in progress \| 100 items in various partial states \| 1 item in progress at a time \|
M|The |tx|\| Feedback speed \| After all 100 are done \| After each one is done \|
M|The |tx|\| Flexibility \| Cannot change approach mid-batch \| Can adapt approach after each item \|
M|The |tx|The envelope experiment has been replicated hundreds of times. Small batches win every time. The advantage increases as complexity increases.
M|Appl|tx|\| Large Batch Startup \| Small Batch Startup \|
M|Appl|tx|\|--------------------\|---------------------\|
M|Appl|tx|\| Spend 6 months building 20 features \| Ship 1 feature, measure, learn, then decide on the nx \|
M|Appl|tx|\| Launch w/ a "complete" pd \| Launch w/ an MVP, iterate based on data \|
M|Appl|tx|\| Conduct a large mk research study, then bd \| Interview 5 cs, bd a tst, interview 5 more \|
M|Appl|tx|\| Write a full business plan, then execute \| tst one assumption, adjust plan, tst the nx \|
M|Appl|tx|\| Redesign the entire app at once \| Change one screen, measure impact, then the nx \|
M|The |**De|** In large batches, a defect in step 1 affects all items processed in steps 2, 3, 4, and 5 before being discovered. In small batches, a defect is caught before it propagates.
M|The |**Qu|** In large batches, each step waits for the entire previous batch to complete. Items spend most of their time waiting, not being worked on. In small batches, items flow continuously.
M|The |**Le|** In large batches, you learn nothing until the entire batch is complete. In small batches, you learn after each item, enabling course correction throughout.
M|Cont|tx|Continuous dpl is the ultimate expression of small batch thinking in software. Every change to the codebase is automatically tested and deployed to production, often multiple times per day.
M|The |tx|```
M|The |tx|Code commit → Automated tests → bd → Staging dp → Automated checks → Production dp → Monitoring
M|The |tx|```
M|Impl|tx|\| Stage \| Description \| Batch Size \| dp Frequency \|
M|Impl|tx|\|-------\|-------------\|------------\|-----------------\|
M|Impl|tx|\| 1. Manual \| Developer packages and deploys manually \| Large (weeks of work) \| Monthly or less \|
M|Impl|tx|\| 2. Scripted \| dp script automates the process \| md (days of work) \| Weekly \|
M|Impl|tx|\| 3. Continuous Integration \| Automated bd and tst on every commit \| Small (hours of work) \| Daily \|
M|Impl|tx|\| 4. Continuous Delivery \| Automated pipeline to staging; manual production trigger \| Very small (single changes) \| Multiple daily \|
M|Impl|tx|\| 5. Continuous dpl \| Fully automated to production \| Minimal (single commit) \| Per commit \|
M|Prer|**Te|**
M|Prer|it|Automated tst suite w/ reasonable coverage (aim for 70%+ of ct paths)
M|Prer|it|Automated bd process
M|Prer|it|Automated dpl scripts
M|Prer|it|Production monitoring and alerting
M|Prer|it|Ability to roll back quickly (under 5 minutes)
M|Prer|**Cu|**
M|Prer|it|Team trusts the automated pipeline
M|Prer|it|Everyone takes responsibility for the bd
M|Prer|it|Broken builds are fixed immediately (not "I'll fix it later")
M|Prer|it|Small commits are valued over large ones
M|Prer|**Pr|**
M|Prer|it|Code rv before merge (pull request workflow)
M|Prer|it|Feature flags for incomplete work
M|Prer|it|Trunk-based dv or short-lived branches
M|Prer|it|On-call rotation for production issues
M|Feat|tx|Feature flags decouple dpl from release. You can dp code to production w/o exposing it to us, then gradually roll it out.
M|Feat|tx|\| tp \| Purpose \| Example \|
M|Feat|tx|\|------\|---------\|---------\|
M|Feat|tx|\| Release flag \| Control when a feature becomes visible \| New dashboard hidden behind flag until ready \|
M|Feat|tx|\| Experiment flag \| Enable A/B testing \| Show new checkout flow to 50% of us \|
M|Feat|tx|\| Ops flag \| Control sy behavior in production \| Disable expensive background job during peak load \|
M|Feat|tx|\| Permission flag \| Restrict access to specific us \| Beta feature available only to internal team \|
M|Prog|tx|\| Phase \| Audience \| Purpose \| Duration \|
M|Prog|tx|\|-------\|----------\|---------\|----------\|
M|Prog|tx|\| 1. Internal \| Team members only \| Catch obvious bugs and UX issues \| 1-3 days \|
M|Prog|tx|\| 2. Beta \| 1-5% of us (early adopters) \| Validate in real conditions w/ sympathetic us \| 3-7 days \|
M|Prog|tx|\| 3. Canary \| 10-25% of us \| Monitor for perf and stability issues \| 3-7 days \|
M|Prog|tx|\| 4. Broad rollout \| 50-100% of us \| Full launch w/ monitoring \| 1-3 days \|
M|Prog|it|[ ] Feature flag is in place and tested (can enable and disable cleanly)
M|Prog|it|[ ] Monitoring dashboard shows feature-specific metrics
M|Prog|it|[ ] Rollback plan is documented and tested
M|Prog|it|[ ] sc metrics are defined for each rollout phase
M|Prog|it|[ ] On-call team is aware of the rollout schedule
M|Prog|it|[ ] cs support team is briefed on the new feature
M|Smal|tx|Small batches apply far beyond software dpl.
M|mk|tx|\| Large Batch \| Small Batch \|
M|mk|tx|\|-------------\|-------------\|
M|mk|tx|\| Plan a 6-month cg, execute all at once \| tst one ad creative per day for a week, then scale winners \|
M|mk|tx|\| Write 30 blog posts, publish all at once \| Write and publish 1 post, measure engagement, adjust topics \|
M|mk|tx|\| Redesign the entire website \| Change one page, measure conversion, iterate \|
M|mk|tx|\| Launch on 5 channels simultaneously \| Start w/ 1 channel, op, then expand \|
M|Sale|tx|\| Large Batch \| Small Batch \|
M|Sale|tx|\|-------------\|-------------\|
M|Sale|tx|\| bd a 50-slide pitch deck, present to 20 prospects \| cr a 5-slide deck, pitch to 3 prospects, revise based on feedback \|
M|Sale|tx|\| Train the entire sales team on a new script \| tst the script w/ 2 reps for a week, refine, then train everyone \|
M|Sale|tx|\| Negotiate all contract terms at once \| Agree on key terms first, then iterate on details \|
M|Hiri|tx|\| Large Batch \| Small Batch \|
M|Hiri|tx|\|-------------\|-------------\|
M|Hiri|tx|\| Write 10 job descriptions, post all, interview in batches \| Post 1 role, refine the process, then post the nx \|
M|Hiri|tx|\| Onboard 5 new hires simultaneously \| Onboard 1 person, learn from their exp, improve for the nx \|
M|Hiri|tx|\| cr an entire employee handbook before hiring \| Document policies as they become relevant \|
M|Prod|tx|\| Large Batch \| Small Batch \|
M|Prod|tx|\|-------------\|-------------\|
M|Prod|tx|\| ds 20 screens in Figma, then hand off to engineering \| ds 1 screen, get engineering feedback, iterate, then nx screen \|
M|Prod|tx|\| Conduct a 50-person usability study \| tst w/ 5 us, fix issues, tst w/ 5 more \|
M|Prod|tx|\| Redesign the entire pd information architecture \| Change 1 navigation element, measure impact, then the nx \|
M|Tech|tx|Break every task into the smallest independently valuable unit.
M|Tech|**Be|** "bd us dashboard" (2 weeks of work)
M|Tech|**Af|**
M|Tech|tx|1. Display us's name and avatar (2 hours)
M|Tech|tx|2. Show account creation date (1 hour)
M|Tech|tx|3. Add usage statistics section (4 hours)
M|Tech|tx|4. Add recent activity feed (6 hours)
M|Tech|tx|5. Add settings shortcuts (3 hours)
M|Tech|tx|Each piece can be deployed, measured, and iterated independently.
M|Tech|tx|Set maximum time limits for work in progress.
M|Tech|tx|\| Context \| Maximum Batch Size \|
M|Tech|tx|\|---------\|-------------------\|
M|Tech|tx|\| Feature dv \| 3 days of work before shipping something \|
M|Tech|tx|\| cs research \| 5 interviews before synthesizing findings \|
M|Tech|tx|\| ds iteration \| 2 days before us testing \|
M|Tech|tx|\| cn creation \| 1 piece before measuring engagement \|
M|Tech|tx|\| Experiment cycles \| 2 weeks before reviewing results \|
M|Tech|tx|Limit the number of items in progress simultaneously.
M|Tech|**Ka|**
M|Tech|tx|\| To Do \| In Progress (max 2) \| In rv (max 1) \| Done \|
M|Tech|tx|\|-------\|---------------------\|-------------------\|------\|
M|Tech|tx|\| Task D \| Task B \| Task A \| ... \|
M|Tech|tx|\| Task E \| Task C \| \| \|
M|Tech|tx|\| Task F \| \| \| \|
M|Tech|tx|When the "In Progress" column is full, no new work starts until something moves to "In rv." This forces completion over starting.
M|Tech|Proc|
M|Tech|tx|1. Pick one us story
M|Tech|tx|2. ds it
M|Tech|tx|3. bd it
M|Tech|tx|4. tst it
M|Tech|tx|5. dp it
M|Tech|tx|6. Measure it
M|Tech|tx|7. Then pick the nx one
M|Tech|tx|This feels slower per item but is faster in total throughput and dramatically faster in learning speed.
M|Depl|tx|\| Tool Category \| Purpose \| Examples \|
M|Depl|tx|\|--------------\|---------\|---------\|
M|Depl|tx|\| CI/CD pipeline \| Automate bd, tst, dp \| GitHub Actions, GitLab CI, CircleCI \|
M|Depl|tx|\| Feature flags \| Decouple dp from release \| LaunchDarkly, Unleash, Flagsmith, Statsig \|
M|Depl|tx|\| Monitoring \| Detect issues immediately after dp \| Datadog, Sentry, PagerDuty, Grafana \|
M|Depl|tx|\| Rollback \| Revert quickly when problems occur \| Built into most CI/CD tools; Kubernetes rollback \|
M|Depl|tx|\| A/B testing \| Compare variations w/ real us \| Optimizely, Statsig, PostHog, GrowthBook \|
M|Proc|tx|\| Tool Category \| Purpose \| Examples \|
M|Proc|tx|\|--------------\|---------\|---------\|
M|Proc|tx|\| Kanban boards \| Visualize flow and WIP limits \| Jira, Linear, Trello, Notion \|
M|Proc|tx|\| Experiment tracking \| Document and track experiments \| Notion, Airtable, custom spreadsheet \|
M|Proc|tx|\| cs feedback \| Collect real-time us input \| Intercom, Hotjar, UserTesting \|
M|Proc|tx|\| an \| Measure impact of each batch \| Amplitude, Mixpanel, PostHog, Google an \|
M|IMVU|IMVU|sometimes a single line of code.
M|IMVU|**Ke|**
M|IMVU|it|Automated tst suite ran on every commit
M|IMVU|- Im|automated monitoring rolled back deploys that degraded key metrics
M|IMVU|it|Engineers deployed their own code (no separate ops team)
M|IMVU|it|Cluster immune sy measured real-time cs behavior after each dp
M|IMVU|**Re|** Problems were caught within minutes. Each dp was so small that root cause al was trivial. The team iterated faster than cr who deployed monthly.
M|Amaz|tx|Amazon decomposed its monolithic application into hundreds of independent services, each owned by a small team (the "two-pizza team" - small enough to feed w/ two pizzas).
M|Amaz|**Ke|**
M|Amaz|it|Each team deploys independently
M|Amaz|it|Services communicate through well-defined APIs
M|Amaz|it|Teams own their service end-to-end (bd, dp, monitor, support)
M|Amaz|- Av|every 11.7 seconds (across the company)
M|Amaz|**Re|** Amazon can ship thousands of changes per day. Each change is small, independently deployable, and independently reversible.
M|Etsy|tx|Etsy transformed from quarterly "big bang" releases to continuous dpl over several years.
M|Etsy|**Be|**
M|Etsy|it|4 deploys per year
M|Etsy|it|Each dp was a massive batch of hundreds of changes
M|Etsy|it|Deploys required multi-day "war rooms" to manage
M|Etsy|it|Bugs were hard to isolate bc so many changes were bundled
M|Etsy|**Af|**
M|Etsy|it|50+ deploys per day
M|Etsy|it|Each dp is a single engineer's change
M|Etsy|it|Deploys take minutes and require no coordination
M|Etsy|it|Bugs are immediately traceable to the single change that caused them
M|Etsy|**Ke|**
M|Etsy|it|Feature flags (Etsy built their own sy, later open-sourced)
M|Etsy|it|Comprehensive monitoring w/ dp annotations
M|Etsy|it|"Push trains" that batch deploys automatically w/ individual rollback capability
M|Etsy|it|Culture of "if it hurts, do it more often"
M|Etsy|The |reducing batch size feels risky but actually reduces risk. The smaller the batch, the faster the feedback, and the faster you learn.